It depend on extent your files get uninstalled. 

Never use apt-get remove python on ubuntu

But if it was not so much, then 

sudo apt-get install --reinstall python2.7
apt-get -f install
sudo apt-get install --reinstall python2.7
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install --reinstall ubuntu-desktop
sudo apt-get install python3-pip (install latest pip)
